Text.Value: Really?!
It's insane you're talking about this. Someone has died.
Yes, you've made that very clear.
And how long has that career been exactly?
Are you enjoying the festival so far?
Oh yes, it's a lovely -
I can get you both some free wine if you'd like.
That's not true at all!
No... I'd imagine not.
I think one's work ethic is far more important than career length, don't you?
Well, I'm glad! It really wasn't easy to set it all up myself.
They're called free samples. We can all get some.
Now, did I mention that I set this entire festival up myself?
Look, I'm just glad no one got hurt.
Makes sense.
No, I mean our business is absolutely ruined.
These barrels aren't light, I'll tell you that for free.
Yes, I suppose the mental harm to that poor old woman would be -
I must say, you're being rather selfish, making this all about you.
How... fascinating. Now, I must say, this vintage is -
I'm just worried about myself - I don't see anything wrong with that.
Do you reckon they'll pay us extra after this terrible scare?
I suppose they might... Hang on.
Who - me? 'Fraid not - I'm a cider man myself.
Say, if you set this up, you probably know the best wine here, right?
If they didn't sell anything, how can they pay more?
I'll tell you for free, I've never seen anything like this in all my career as a festival worker.
Indeed, that poor halfling couple nearly died!

Synopsis: When the Wine Festival begins, some ADs will be playing in row. This is one of them.
